    <h2>JavaScript</h2>
    <p>
      <span id="first" class="js">JavaScript</span> (/ˈdʒɑːvəˌskrɪpt/),[8] often
      abbreviated as JS, <span>is</span> a programming language that conforms to
      the ECMAScript specification.[9] <span class="js">JavaScript</span>
      <span>is</span> high-level, often just-in-time compiled,
      <span>and</span> multi-paradigm. It has curly-bracket syntax, dynamic
      typing, prototype-based object-orientation, <span>and</span> first-class
      functions.
